schema.headline: Magic Round live: Canterbury Bulldogs vs Canberra Raiders, Manly Sea Eagles vs Brisbane Broncos — NRL scores, stats and results

liveBlogUpdate.headline: We'll get back to regularly scheduled programming
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: We'll end this live moment there, now that the game has settled into a rhythm. Our ScoreCentre will stay live as always, and you can tune in on ABC Radio .

liveBlogUpdate.headline: The Raiders hit back
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: Jack Wighton perfectly weights a chip over the top and Xavier Savage shows great patience to wait for the bounce, gather and put down. Croker misses the conversion, but the shootout is on.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Most Magikal score?
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: What's the record score for a Magic Round game? Are we on here? - Dave. Well Dave, the Storm kicked the tar out of the Eels 64-10 in the first Magic Round in 2019. Don't see that sort of thing happening tonight.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Mahoney Magic
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: The Bulldogs hooker comes up with a momentum-shifting 40/20 out of dummy half. Then lays on a try with a perfect short ball for back rower Jacob Preston, who juggled before regathered just in time to ground the ball. Mahoney really has injected some class into this team from a pivotal position.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Bulldogs get their first touch five minutes into the game
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: It was initially ruled a dropout and overturned by the bunker. So, we should settle into a more normal rhythm, but the Dogs are playing from behind now.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Alan Jones is up in the Raiders' box
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: He's perched behind Ricky Stuart. All the stars are in Brisbane this weekend.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Another shocker from the Bulldogs
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: Another kick to Casey, this time he takes it, but just hands it straight back to Rapana. Awful start for the Canterbury winger.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: TRY FROM THE FIRST SET. IN THE FIRST MINUTE!
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: Whoa ho ho, it's MAGIC! Truly shocking from the Bulldogs, with Jamal Fogarty's pedestrian cross-field bomb just basically ignored by the Dogs' Paul Alimoti, Declan Casey and Matt Burton, allowing Jordan Rapana a free grab, which he happily took and just fell over the line.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Here come the first teams of the weekend
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: The Raiders get a pretty warm welcome and the Bulldogs, with Matt Burton rocking the number seven, get more than a few boos. Here we go. And Burton's kick-off sails into the arms of Canberra's Jack Wighton. The two star attractions in this match combining immediately.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: What to expect this weekend
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: There are a few highlight matches clearly over the next three days. The Broncos and Sea Eagles is the headline act tonight pretty obviously. Tomorrow we've got Brisbane's own 'Phins taking on the in-form Sharks in the evening game, before the slick Rabbitohs face the perennially contending Storm in the night match. And on Sunday, the 4pm game pits the Roosters against the Cowboys, making sure Queensland teams feature on every day. (The Titans are also here.)

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Who's missing?
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: I said in that previous post that every team is in Brisbane, but that's just a straight-up lie. The Newcastle Knights are nowhere in sight. They were the unlucky team to get the bye in round 10 when the draw came out before the season, although it's proven to be a good call because, as was the case in 2022, they look aimless this season.

liveBlogUpdate.headline: Magic Round is here
liveBlogUpdate.articleBody: It's the most anticipated round on the rugby league calendar since the opening week, and it's here! As they did last year, the Bulldogs are getting the ball rolling, but it shouldn't be as much of a slog this time around, with their clash against the Raiders promising plenty of fireworks.
